description.para: These don't do anything anymore but are left for backwards compatibility

briefdescription.para: API to interact with Central Economy.

simplesect.para: Accessible through GetCEApi, make sure to read the documentation for that as well
Any mention of 'storage/' means the '$mission:storage_#' folder
Only exists when the game has CE enabled
This means that this will work on anything which is running a mission with an initialized Hive
Client does not have Hive when connected to a server, only the server does if it was set up in the init.c
type="0"

parameterdescription.para: string The name of the entry

simplesect.para: int The value or int.MIN if not found/not an int
type="1"

parameterdescription.para: string The name of the entry

simplesect.para: float The value or float.MIN if not found/not a float
type="2"

parameterdescription.para: string The name of the entry

simplesect.para: string The value or empty string if not found/not a string

description.para: Optimized internal methods that the CE uses to avoid spawning DE within certain distances

briefdescription.para: Check if there is a player within a radius.

parameterdescription.para: vector The center point
float The radius around the center point

simplesect.para: bool Returns false when there is a player inside supplied area, true when it successfully avoided players GetCEApi().AvoidPlayer(Vector(500,0,500),20);

briefdescription.para: Check if there is a vehicle within a radius.

parameterdescription.para: vector The center point
float The radius around the center point
string A specific DE to avoid, if left empty, will avoid all vehicles

simplesect.para: bool Returns false when there is a vehicle inside supplied area, true when it successfully avoided vehicles GetCEApi().AvoidVehicle(Vector(500,0,500),500,"VehicleCivilianSedan");

briefdescription.para: Check if there is a vehicle within a radius.

parameterdescription.para: vector The center point
float The radius around the center point

simplesect.para: int The amoutn of players inside supplied area GetCEApi().CountPlayersWithinRange(Vector(500,0,500),500);

description.para: DIAG ONLY: These options are available from the in-game debug menu on Diag exe (Game > Central Economy), documentation can be found on wiki

briefdescription.para: Lists stats regarding which loot spawn) that are linked together and how many there are.

simplesect.para: In logs: "[linked_groups]"

briefdescription.para: Lists loot spawns that have more loot than their maximum + 4.

simplesect.para: In logs: "[autotest:ListSuspiciousGroups]"

briefdescription.para: Lists DE spawns that have positions that are within supplied range (< fRange, not equal)

simplesect.para: In logs: "[ClosePosition]"

briefdescription.para: Lists loot spawns that have been marked as abandoned.

simplesect.para: In logs: "[autotest:ListAbandonedGroups]"

briefdescription.para: Lists loot spawns that are not abandoned but have no loot.

simplesect.para: In logs: "[autotest:ListEmptyGroups]"

briefdescription.para: Lists loot spawns that are not abandoned and within the supplied range (< fRange, not equal)

simplesect.para: In logs: "[autotest:ListCloseGroups]"
Is the same as CEApi.ListCloseProxy

briefdescription.para: Lists the number of objects inside of categories.

simplesect.para: In logs: "[autotest:ProcessDebugLog]"
In logs: "[autotest:OverallStatus]"

briefdescription.para: Lists the maxlootsize of all CE items.

simplesect.para: In logs: "[autotest:ListLootSize]"

briefdescription.para: Generates string that will make CEApi.EconomyMap use all items with this category.

simplesect.para: This is refering to the CE categories of loot defined in cfglimitsdefinition.xml
This is persistent per session, when you set it, it will persist until it is set to something else

parameterdescription.para: string The desired loot category

simplesect.para: string The string to pass into CEApi.EconomyMap GetCEApi().EconomyMap(EconomyMapStrings.Category("food"));

briefdescription.para: Generates string that will make CEApi.EconomyMap use all items with this tag.

simplesect.para: This is refering to the CE tags of loot defined in cfglimitsdefinition.xml
This is persistent per session, when you set it, it will persist until it is set to something else

parameterdescription.para: string The desired loot tag

simplesect.para: string The string to pass into CEApi.EconomyMap GetCEApi().EconomyMap(EconomyMapStrings.Tag("floor"));
Already happens automatically when server starts before it is loaded in GetCEApi().ExportSpawnData();

parameterdescription.para: vector Center of area to generate from

simplesect.para: When using a zero vector, this will automatically get the world center

parameterdescription.para: float Radius in meters of area to generate from

simplesect.para: When 0, this will automatically get a radius covering the map //Exportforwholemap GetCEApi().ExportProxyData();

briefdescription.para: Invalidates loot spawn points which are closer than the radius supplied.

simplesect.para: Will output a message indicating how many points were invalidated

parameterdescription.para: float The minimum desired distance in meters between loot spawn points

simplesect.para: When 0 it will use a radius of 0.5

parameterdescription.para: bool When false, will only check the points within a container against each other, when true will against all points //Example:Iwanttheretobeaminimumdistanceof0.3mbetweenanylootspawnpoint GetCEApi().MarkCloseProxy(0.3,true);

simplesect.para: Is best paired with a MarkCloseProxy call first to invalidate unwanted points
Will output a message indicating the amount of deleted points GetCEApi().RemoveCloseProxy();

briefdescription.para: Outputs a list of all loot points closer than specified radius.

simplesect.para: This will automatically be checking all points against all points
This is a better way of handling it than the above two methods, as it can be then be removed manually from the xmls
Is the same as CEApi.EconomyOutput(EconomyOutputStrings.CLOSE, fRadius)

parameterdescription.para: float The minimum desired distance in meters between loot spawn points GetCEApi().ListCloseProxy(0.3);

briefdescription.para: Will emulate the spawning of the item which is being looked at and generate images (.tga) in storage/lmap and output logs.

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
This will only work if the loot spawner is active

parameterdescription.para: string The class name of the desired item to analyze

simplesect.para: When using "*" as class name, instead of generating images, it will generate a .csv in storage/log containing the output of all spawnable items
bool Whether the operation was successful, it might fail in certain scenarios if the CE doesn't update in time GetCEApi().SpawnAnalyze("FlatCap_Grey");

briefdescription.para: Subtracts the supplied value from the current lifetime of all items in the world.

simplesect.para: Uses RadiusLifetimeDecrease under the hood and then calculates the parameters to fit the world
Will automatically clamp result between min and max lifetime [3, 316224000] (3 seconds to 10 years)

parameterdescription.para: float The value in seconds which will be subtracted from the current lifetimes //Shortensthelifetimesofallitemsintheworldby3seconds GetCEApi().TimeShift(3);

briefdescription.para: Fills in the Debug Lifetime, which will be used for any new DE spawned.

parameterdescription.para: float The lifetime for any DE spawned after this call

simplesect.para: When this is set back to 0, it will stop using the Debug Lifetime //AnyDEspawnedafterthiscallwillhavealifetimeof300seconds GetCEApi().OverrideLifeTime(300);

briefdescription.para: Force spawn specific prototype group + loot at position.

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
This can also spawn in other CE & DE related objects, but is best used exclusively for testing prototype groups

parameterdescription.para: string The group name to spawn
vector The position to spawn the Entity at
float Angle to spawn the Entity with in degrees [0, 360]

simplesect.para: When a negative value, will pick a random one
Entity The spawned Entity or null if unsuccessful GetCEApi().SpawnGroup("Land_Shed_M1",Vector(5,10,5));
DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
Versatile, can be used for Animal, Infected, Static, Item and Vehicle
Is the only one capable of spawning DE's that have DE Groups
Is the same as the next one, but has ECE_FULL flags and a hidden flag which overrides herd limit
This is also FORCE spawn, so it will bypass any limit and avoidance checks

parameterdescription.para: string The DE to spawn
vector The position to spawn the Entity at
float Angle to spawn the Entity with in degrees [0, 360]

simplesect.para: When a negative value, will pick a random one
bool Whether the spawn was successful GetCEApi().SpawnDE("StaticHeliCrash",Vector(5,10,5));

memberdef.argsstring: (string sEvName, vector vPos, float fAngle, int uFlags)
memberdef.name: SpawnDEEx

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
Is the same one as above but with the possibility of custom flags

parameterdescription.para: string The DE to spawn
vector The position to spawn the Entity at
float Angle to spawn the Entity with in degrees [0, 360]

simplesect.para: When a negative value, will pick a random one

parameterdescription.para: int ECE flags to apply while spawning the DE

simplesect.para: bool Whether the spawn was successful GetCEApi().SpawnDEEx("StaticHeliCrash",Vector(5,10,5),ECE_FULL);

memberdef.argsstring: (string sEvName, vector vPos, float fAngle, int iCount=1, float fRange=1)
memberdef.name: SpawnLoot

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY

parameterdescription.para: string The DE to spawn
vector The position to spawn the Entity at
float Angle to spawn the Entity with in degrees [0, 360]

simplesect.para: When a negative value, will pick a random one

parameterdescription.para: int The amount of items
float Circle radius

simplesect.para: When iCount is larger than 1, changing this will make it so that they are spawned in a circle around vPos GetCEApi().SpawnLoot("Deagle",Vector(5,10,5),0,9,1);

briefdescription.para: Spawn all entities with dynamic category through CE.

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
Will print additional logs to RPT

parameterdescription.para: vector The position to spawn the Entities at

simplesect.para: This will be the starting position, the items will be split into segments by CE BBox size (smallest to largest)

parameterdescription.para: bool Whether to draw the CE BBox with debug shapes

simplesect.para: Red: Invalid BBox; Yellow: Not in DB; Green: All ok

parameterdescription.para: float The default distance to use when the entity does not have a CE BBox

simplesect.para: This means that all the ones with invalid CE BBoxes will be piled up at the starting position when this is 0 GetCEApi().SpawnDynamic(Vector(5,10,5),true);

briefdescription.para: Spawn all entities with vehicles category through CE.

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
Will print additional logs to RPT

parameterdescription.para: vector The position to spawn the Entities at

simplesect.para: This will be the starting position, vehicles spawn with 20m spacing
Make sure you do it on a surface as flat and open as possible, they need a lot of space

parameterdescription.para: bool Does nothing for Vehicles, left for backwards compat
float The default distance to use when the entity does not have a CE BBox

simplesect.para: This means that all the ones with invalid CE BBoxes will be piled up at the starting position when this is 0 GetCEApi().SpawnVehicles(Vector(5,10,5));

briefdescription.para: Spawn all entities with building category through CE.

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
Will print additional logs to RPT

parameterdescription.para: vector The position to spawn the Entities at

simplesect.para: This will be the starting position, the items will be split into segments by CE BBox size (smallest to largest)

parameterdescription.para: bool Whether to draw the CE BBox with debug shapes

simplesect.para: Red: Invalid BBox; Yellow: Not in DB; Green: All ok
These will most likely just always be red

parameterdescription.para: float The default distance to use when the entity does not have a CE BBox

simplesect.para: This means that all the ones with invalid CE BBoxes will be piled up at the starting position when this is 0 GetCEApi().SpawnBuilding(Vector(5,10,5),true);

memberdef.argsstring: (string sClassName, vector vPos, float fRange, int iCount)
memberdef.name: SpawnEntity

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
Is similar to SpawnLoot, but works better on Animal/Infected/Vehicle

parameterdescription.para: string The entity to spawn
vector The position to spawn the Entity at
float Circle radius

simplesect.para: When iCount is larger than 1, changing this will make it so that they are spawned in a circle around vPos

parameterdescription.para: int The amount of items GetCEApi().SpawnEntity("Deagle",Vector(5,10,5),1,9);

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
Is the same as SpawnEntity, but spawns only one and returns the spawned Object

parameterdescription.para: string The entity to spawn
vector The position to spawn the Entity at

simplesect.para: Object The spawned Object GetCEApi().SpawnSingleEntity("Deagle",Vector(5,10,5));

memberdef.argsstring: (string sClassName, vector vPos, float fRange, int iCount, int iFlags)
memberdef.name: SpawnRotation

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
Is the same as SpawnEntity, under the hood it just defaults to RF_ORIGINAL

parameterdescription.para: string The entity to spawn
vector The position to spawn the Entity at
float Circle radius

simplesect.para: When iCount is larger than 1, changing this will make it so that they are spawned in a circle around vPos

parameterdescription.para: int The amount of items
int The rotation flags to apply GetCEApi().SpawnRotation("Deagle",Vector(5,10,5),1,9,RF_ALL);

briefdescription.para: Spawn an entity through CE, x amount of times in a grid.

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
The name may imply it does something else, but a profiler is needed to actually benchmark it
The position starts at 0 0 0

parameterdescription.para: string The entity to spawn
int The amount of items GetCEApi().SpawnPerfTest("Deagle",30);

briefdescription.para: Queue up the depleting of lifetime of everything in the world.

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY GetCEApi().CleanMap();
DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY

parameterdescription.para: string The type of log (EconomyLogCategories) GetCEApi().EconomyLog(EconomyLogCategories.Economy);

briefdescription.para: Outputs debug file to storage/lmap/*.tga showing the current places this is spawned.

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY
This works best when you have an image of the map to overlay the tga with afterwards

parameterdescription.para: string The type of lmap, can be just a class name or a special string

simplesect.para: There are several prefixes and sets of strings that can be passed in here, see EconomyMapStrings //Tocheckonlyaspecificitem GetCEApi().EconomyMap("Deagle");

briefdescription.para: Outputs debug logs into server log or rpt.

simplesect.para: DEVELOPER/DIAG ONLY

parameterdescription.para: string One of the strings specified in EconomyOutputStrings
float Range parameter used for some of the options GetCEApi().EconomyOutput(EconomyOutputStrings.CLOSE,3);

briefdescription.para: Process lifetime increase within radius by value (sec)

simplesect.para: Will automatically clamp result between min and max lifetime [3, 316224000] (3 seconds to 10 years)

parameterdescription.para: vector The center point
float The radius around the center point
float The value to increase the lifetime by

simplesect.para: When 0, this will reset it to default instead (but it's better to use RadiusLifetimeReset still) GetCEApi().RadiusLifetimeIncrease(Vector(500,0,500),3,500);

briefdescription.para: Process lifetime decrease within radius by value (sec)

simplesect.para: Will automatically clamp result between min and max lifetime [3, 316224000] (3 seconds to 10 years)

parameterdescription.para: vector The center point
float The radius around the center point
float The value to decrease the lifetime by GetCEApi().RadiusLifetimeDecrease(Vector(500,0,500),3,500);

briefdescription.para: Process lifetime reset to default value from DB within radius.

parameterdescription.para: vector The center point
float The radius around the center point GetCEApi().RadiusLifetimeReset(Vector(500,0,500),3);
